ISLAMABAD, Nov. 13 (Xinhua) -- Two policemen were killed when a bomb went off in Pakistan's northwest Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province on Saturday, said police officials. A police van was passing by the Raghagan Dam area of Bajaur tribal district of the province when it came under attack by militants, killing two policemen, Bajaur District Police Officer Abdul Samad Khan told Xinhua. The official said that the police party was the target of the explosion, adding that the blast was conducted via a remote control device. Following the explosion, law enforcement agencies along with rescue teams reached the site and cordoned off the area to initiate a preliminary investigation. No militant group or individual has claimed the attack yet. Enditem